Nebulous Rules
 
 1. Do not share or trade accounts with anyone. This will result in both players being permanently banned.
 2. Do not ask for accounts from anyone. This will result in you being permanently banned.
 3. Do not pretend to be a Moderator or Youtuber. This will result in you being permanently banned.
 4. Do not cheat to reach the top ranking of the game in clan wars or arenas (FreePoints). This will reset your stats and result in a permanent ban.
 5. Never ask for the leader rank in a Clan.
 6. Do not insult anyone.
 7. Do not create Custom Games or Chats with inappropriate names.
 8. Obey the Moderators.
 9. Do not take advantage of bugs in the game.
 10. Do not ban many clan members without the leader's authorization or consent.
 11. In team games, do not team up with someone that does not belong to your team.
 12. Never lie to a Moderator.
 13. Do not exchange Nebulous Clans for real money or plasma.
 14. Do not spam in chat or mail.
 
 If you do not comply with any of these rules, your account may be banned or muted.
 (The time of punishment can vary between a few hours and a permanent ban or mute, depending of the situation and severity of the problem).
 
 If you notice a player breaking the rules of the game, please do not hesitate on reporting it to a Moderator.

"CUSTOM SKINS
When you upload a custom skin, the image quality will decrease, but this doesn\'t matter too much and is common (you may not notice significant difference while you play).
In Review (Yellow Highlight): This means your skin is being reviewed by our moderation team. You must wait for it to be approved.
Approved (Green Highlight): This means your skin meets the established Custom Skin Guidelines and can be viewed by other players.
Refunded (Orange Highlight): This means you received a refund of the skin, because it does not meet the established guidelines. You must not try to upload the same skin or one that contains similar violations.
Rejected (Red Highlight): This means your skin cannot be viewed by other players because of the inappropriate content on it. You will have your plasma lost, unlike the refunded case.
WHY DID MY CUSTOM SKIN GET REFUNDED OR REJECTED?
If your custom skin is refunded, you should not attempt on uploading the same again, otherwise your plasma will be lost.
This is a list of content that are *PROHIBITED* to use in the custom skins: - Skins that contain sexual references - Skins that contain already existing Nebulous arts (such as level, achievement, season, plasma, pets or exclusive pack skins) - Skins that contain gore/suicidal references - Shirtless/Nude skins - Very dark skins - Totally transparent skins (unidentifiable) - Skins that contain drugs (alcohol/cigarettes/marijuana) - Skins that contain NSFW pages - Skins that contain necklines on the body - Skins that contain racism/nazism/violence references - Skins that contain people using a weapon - Skins that contain obscene signals with hands (it may vary depending of the region, so be vehemently careful with cases like that).
If you attempt on uploading a skin with that contains the items listed above, it will be refunded or rejected."
